CARAPACE (
Fig. 22A
). Cephalic area highest in lateral view and steep vertical slopes in frontal view; uniformly dark reddish-brown with indistinct darker radial pattern; covered with dark brown setae,

STERNUM (
Fig. 22B
). Dark reddish-brown with grey pigmentation; covered with brown setae that are longer towards margins.

ABDOMEN. Dorsally yellow-brown with indistinct lanceolate heart mark in anterior half; olive-grey mottled pattern in anterior half that forms transverse bars in posterior half; covered with grey setae (
Fig. 22A
). Ventrally yellow-brown with olive-grey central patch that dissolves with yellow-brown spots laterally; three longitudinal bands of dense white setae. Spinnerets light brown (
Fig. 22B
).

CARAPACE AND EYES (
Fig 22C
). As male.

STERNUM (
Fig. 22D
). As male, but with less grey pigmentation.

ABDOMEN. Poorly preserved; dorsal pattern as male but lighter (
Fig. 22C
). Venter light yellow-brown with a large grey central patch through darker setae. Spinnerets as male (
Fig. 22D
).

EPIGYNE. Ventral view (
Fig. 23D
): circular atrium with anterior notch. Dorsal view (
Fig. 23E
): spermathecal heads cylindrical with indistinct spermathecal stalks.
